{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013PGk1iDTJic6mgNU7Uqs6M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to:\n1. Delete the existing StatefulSet (it uses wrong image) and PVCs (they have 7.x data which is incompatible with 8.x)\n2. Generate TLS certificates\n3. Create es-http-tls and elastic-password secrets\n4. Create new ConfigMap for ES 8.11.1 \n5. Create new StatefulSet for ES 8.11.1 with TLS\n\nThe services can remain as-is.\n\nLet me plan the approach:\n\n**Step 1**: Generate TLS certificates using openssl\n**Step 2**: Create the secrets for TLS and authentication\n**Step 3**: Remove the old StatefulSet and PVCs since the 7.x data won't work with 8.x\n**Step 4**: Update the ConfigMap with ES 8.11.1 settings, enabling security with transport and HTTP TLS, and configuring the initial master nodes\n**Step 5**: Deploy the new StatefulSet\n\nFor the password setup, I'll use the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable to bootstrap the elastic user with a known password like \"changeme\". The plan involves generating CA and node certificates with proper SANs for the cluster DNS names, creating the TLS secret with the certificates, setting up the password secret, then deploying the updated configuration.\n\nFor the ConfigMap, I'm setting up the Elasticsearch 8.x configuration with the cluster name, node roles (master, data, ingest), network binding, and discovery settings pointing to the three nodes in the cluster with their fully qualified domain names, plus the initial master nodes list.\n\nNow I'm adding the security configuration with X-Pack enabled, setting up TLS for both transport and HTTP layers using the certificate files mounted from the secret, and disabling memory mapping for compatibility.\n\nFor the StatefulSet, I need to mount the TLS certificates from the es-http-tls secret, inject the ELASTIC_PASSWORD environment variable from the elastic-password secret, and use the Elasticsearch 8.11.1 image. For the readiness probe, I'm using an exec command that curls the cluster health endpoint with authentication to verify the cluster is ready.\n\nActually, a simpler tcpSocket probe on port 9200 should work fine for initial deployment since it just checks if the port is listening. I also need to set `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap the 3-node cluster with the pod names es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, and es-cluster-2.\n\nFor discovery, I should use the fully qualified DNS names of the headless service to be safe, though the short names within the namespace would work too. I'm noticing the ConfigMap seed_hosts might have drifted to invalid values, so I need to verify those are correct.\n\nNow I'll start generating the TLS certificates using openssl commands.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3826,"cache_read_input_tokens":35491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3826},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6fee40c-37c1-4d91-87ea-459dca2dc3bc","uuid":"da05cada-8153-4a1f-9199-7912febb7f17","request_id":"req_011Ccg7z68iCCv6gm4G3ozuU"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013PGk1iDTJic6mgNU7Uqs6M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The current deployment uses ES 7.17.9 (wrong image, no TLS). I need to tear it down and redeploy with 8.11.1 + HTTPS. Starting with TLS cert generation and secrets."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3826,"cache_read_input_tokens":35491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3826},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6fee40c-37c1-4d91-87ea-459dca2dc3bc","uuid":"cb76931a-d52a-436b-8a16-4cee5c791d9b","request_id":"req_011Ccg7z68iCCv6gm4G3ozuU"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013PGk1iDTJic6mgNU7Uqs6M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FGRqsdjM61Nv4eGBncLmB3","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp && mkdir -p es-certs && cd es-certs && \\\n  # Generate CA key and cert\n  openssl genrsa -out ca.key 2048 2>/dev/null && \\\n  openssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key ca.key -sha256 -days 3650 -out ca.crt \\\n    -subj \"/CN=elasticsearch-ca/O=elastic\" 2>/dev/null && \\\n  # Generate node key\n  openssl genrsa -out tls.key 2048 2>/dev/null && \\\n  # Generate CSR with SANs covering all cluster DNS names\n  cat > san.ext << 'EOF'\n[req]\nreq_extensions = v3_req\ndistinguished_name = req_distinguished_name\n[req_distinguished_name]\n[v3_req]\nsubjectAltName = @alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1 = localhost\nDNS.2 = es-cluster\nDNS.3 = es-cluster-0.es-cluster\nDNS.4 = es-cluster-1.es-cluster\nDNS.5 = es-cluster-2.es-cluster\nDNS.6 = es-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.7 = es-cluster-1.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.8 = es-cluster-2.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.9 = es-http\nDNS.10 = es-http.elasticsearch\nDNS.11 = es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nIP.1 = 127.0.0.1\nEOF\n  openssl req -new -key tls.key -out tls.csr \\\n    -subj \"/CN=es-cluster/O=elastic\" \\\n    -config san.ext 2>/dev/null && \\\n  openssl x509 -req -in tls.csr -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key -CAcreateserial \\\n    -out tls.crt -days 3650 -sha256 -extfile san.ext -extensions v3_req 2>/dev/null && \\\n  echo \"Cert generated OK\" && \\\n  openssl x509 -in tls.crt -text -noout | grep -A2 \"Subject Alternative Name\"","description":"Generate self-signed CA and node TLS certificates with SANs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3826,"cache_read_input_tokens":35491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_token