{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NU25kFxWoS2TWT77yFShrP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem**: The namespace had a pre-existing ES 7.17.9 deployment with no TLS and missing required secrets.\n\n**Actions taken**:\n1. Generated a self-signed CA and node TLS certificate (SANs covering all cluster DNS names)\n2. Created `es-http-tls` secret (ca.crt, tls.crt, tls.key)\n3. Created `elastic-password` secret (password: `elastic123!`)\n4. Deleted the incompatible 7.17.9 StatefulSet and its PVCs\n5. Replaced `es-config` ConfigMap with ES 8.11.1 config: xpack.security enabled, transport + HTTP TLS, `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, fully-qualified `discovery.seed_hosts`\n6. Deployed new StatefulSet with image `elasticsearch:8.11.1`, mounting certs from the secret and reading the elastic password from the secret\n\n**Verification**:\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`\n- Cluster health: `green`, 3 nodes, 3 data nodes\n- HTTPS via `es-http:9200` works with `elastic` credentials\n- Write and read of a document succeeded"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":616,"cache_read_input_tokens":45521,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":616},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6fee40c-37c1-4d91-87ea-459dca2dc3bc","uuid":"930d4d32-cafc-4096-96ab-7c9b2119e275","request_id":"req_011Ccg8Fjzwxph6Tyy6URmR9"}
